text: Jorge Scibona (May 9, 1931 â€“ February 10, 2021), known professionally as Jorge Morel, was an Argentine classical guitarist and composer. Morel was born in Buenos Aires. Morel appeared at Lincoln Center's Alice Tully Hall in New York, Queen Elizabeth Hall and Wigmore Hall in London, National Concert Hall in Dublin, and Suntory Hall in Tokyo.
